The movies were fine once I got them to play. There was no sound when I tried to play each movie on my DVD player. I tried Myvern on the computer and there was sound. I found this annoying as I always watch my movie on the DVD player. The movies themselves were great. I have no problem with their quality. Just wish they worked on the DVD player. If you don't have a computer that plays movies you might want to consider passing on this set!

These are some of the better movies that run on the SyFy Channel. And a couple, like Wyvvern and Road Kill, are top-notch. To be sure, these movies aren't for everybody. But if you like cookin' up some popcorn and kicking back to watch some whup-ass monster fun, these movies will do the trick.

This is a great set of B-grade sci-fi movies for the price. I it is a three-disc set, so the set comes with two movies on each of disc. The quality is good. I'm an old man, and watching these movies is like watching the classic B-grade sci-fi flicks of the 1950s that I grew up on watching at the local Saturday afternoon monster movie double feature. Corny but great fun!
